Getting ICU4c
=====

On Linux:


cd /tmp
wget http://download.icu-project.org/files/icu4c/51.2/icu4c-51_2-src.tgz
tar -zxvf icu4c-51_2-src.tgz
....TODO: download FULL ICU data & decompress it to icu/source/data.....
cd icu/source/
./configure
make
sudo make install     # as root


Perhaps this also will be required:

sudo [edit_cmd] /etc/ld.so.conf

or:

sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicuuc.so.51.2 /usr/lib    # or .so.XX.XX (check!)
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicui18n.so.51.2  /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicudata.so.51.2  /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicuio.so.51.2 /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicule.so.51.2 /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libiculx.so.51.2 /usr/lib

Then update ld-database/cache:

sudo ldconfig



On Fedora Linux:

   you may try with `yum install libicu-devel`
   however, it may give you an outdated version of the ICU library
   therefore, it is not recommended



On Windows:

See: http://site.icu-project.org/download/51#TOC-ICU4C-Download

